{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":122896,"duration_api_ms":192789,"num_turns":7,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"27c672c9-6528-4314-88c6-17da6e3c16d7","total_cost_usd":0.5326527499999999,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":29845,"cache_read_input_tokens":118382,"output_tokens":3803,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":29845,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":203,"outputTokens":9907,"cacheReadInputTokens":795875,"cacheCreationInputTokens":50004,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.19183050000000004,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":5,"outputTokens":3803,"cacheReadInputTokens":118382,"cacheCreationInputTokens":29845,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.34082225,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"Reviewed all four amendments against the source code. The two state-management defects (fr-5-15b1f41e and fr-5-ef6f1e4a) are real bugs confirmed by code inspection. The timestamp fallback concern (fr-5-54b32534) is inherent to legacy data and the suggestion doesn't materially improve safety. The double-collapse concern (fr-5-3ee9bde4) is a minor idempotent performance issue, not a correctness defect.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-5-54b32534","decision":"reject","rationale":"The wildcard arm in `same_attempt` already only fires when at least one side lacks a `run_id`, which is the legacy case. The false-positive scenario requires two distinct runs for the same bead/project to share an identical `started_at` timestamp *and* one to lack a `run_id` — an extremely unlikely coincidence bound by the legacy data model's inherent ambiguity. The suggested tightening is effectively what the code already does, and the suggestion to add a comment is documentation polish, not a correctness fix. No actionable change improves safety here."},{"amendment_id":"fr-5-3ee9bde4","decision":"reject","rationale":"`collapse_task_run_attempts` is idempotent — running it twice on the same data produces identical results with no side effects. Keeping `reconcile_snapshot_from_lineage` self-contained (calling collapse internally at line 140) means every caller gets a correctly reconciled snapshot without needing to pre-collapse. Changing its signature to accept pre-collapsed data would create a fragile contract where callers must remember to collapse first, for a negligible performance gain on a small in-memory list. This is a clean design trade-off, not a defect."},{"amendment_id":"fr-5-15b1f41e","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed by reading lines 176-189: the `else if` branch only converts `Active → Ready` when no active bead exists. If `record_bead_start` crashes after appending a Running lineage entry (line 469) but before `write_snapshot` (line 480), the snapshot remains in whatever status it had before (e.g., `Planning`). When a later completion repair runs `reconcile_snapshot_from_lineage`, it finds no active bead (the run completed) but the status is `Planning` not `Active`, so the conversion branch is skipped. The milestone stays stuck in `Planning` permanently despite all beads having finished. Reconciliation should derive the correct idle status from lineage state (no active bead → Ready) regardless of the prior snapshot status."},{"amendment_id":"fr-5-ef6f1e4a","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed classic TOCTOU race: `read_task_runs` at line 388 is unlocked, the idempotence check at lines 392-423 runs in memory, and `append_task_run` at line 469 acquires a file lock only for the atomic append. Two concurrent retries of the same (bead_id, project_id, run_id) can both observe 'no existing row', both pass the check, and both append Running entries. Similarly, the journal dedupe at lines 485-488 is another unlocked read-then-append. While `collapse_task_run_attempts` can later merge duplicate lineage rows, duplicate `BeadStarted` journal events are permanent and snapshot counts are temporarily wrong. The entire read-check-append sequence for start idempotence needs to execute under a single lock."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"a80785c4-d93c-4a1b-a28a-56669191338d"}
